# Anti-Patterns — NEVER Do These

## Preservation Rules (CRITICAL)
- NEVER modify a file unless explicitly instructed to
- NEVER refactor, rename, or reorganize existing working code while implementing a new feature
- NEVER change existing component prop signatures or API response handling
- NEVER add or remove Zustand store fields without explicit instruction
- ALWAYS ask before touching:
  - src/app/(auth)/login/page.js
  - src/store/store.js
  - src/utils/routes.js
  - src/utils/apiRoutes.js
  - src/lib/apolloClient.js

## React Anti-Patterns
- NEVER use array index as key in lists that can reorder or update
- NEVER add useEffect for data fetching in modules that already use SWR or Apollo
- NEVER introduce new state management libraries — Zustand is the standard
- NEVER use class components
- NEVER use `var` — use `const` or `let`

## Next.js Anti-Patterns
- NEVER use `<img>` tag — use `next/image`
- NEVER use `<a>` tag for internal navigation — use `next/link`
- NEVER add `'use client'` to a file that doesn't need browser APIs or interactivity

## API / Data Fetching Anti-Patterns
- NEVER hardcode API URLs inline in components — use apiPath from routes.js
- NEVER mix GraphQL and REST for the same feature
- NEVER introduce a new data fetching pattern (e.g. React Query, useSWR) outside the Notes module without explicit approval

## Code Style
- NEVER use TypeScript syntax in .js/.jsx files
- NEVER leave console.log statements in committed code
- NEVER add unused imports or variables
